actions:
- author: matthew
  body: In general, we need to think through and finalise the semantics for power level ACLs - e.g. should users of the same power level be able to kick each other?  Should I be able to delegate my power level to anyone, or do I need a threshold to do so, and if so does the target need to have less power than me already? etc.
  created: 2015-06-16 12:28:11.0
  id: '11866'
  issue: '10780'
  type: comment
  updateauthor: matthew
  updated: 2015-06-16 12:28:11.0
- author: erikj
  body: |-
    You shouldn't be able to affect (e.g. kick/ban/change power level) any other user with greater *or equal* power level to your own. Everything else can remain as it is for now.

    We need to add a power level option for the "clear history" flag and whether users can see history for before they join.
